ZCZC OE54
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 162300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING A LARGE DEEP LOW PRESSURE 974 WILL EXTEND A CYCLONIC
INFLUENCE ACROSS A LARGE MAJORITY OF THE N ATLANTIC. THIS LOW WILL EXTEND
A TROUGH OF LOW PRESSURE EWARDS TOWARD THE CELTIC SEA AND ANOTHER S TOWARD
THE AZORES. THE PARENT LOW WILL MAKE ERRATIC PROGRESS N AND W THROUGH TUESDAY
AS NEW DISCRETE LOW PRESSURES ARE SPAWNED IN THE MID-ATLANTIC AND MIGRATE
E TOWARD THE BRITISH ISLES. INTO WEDNESDAY THE PARENT LOW WILL ALSO MIGRATE
E ACROSS THE BRITISH ISLES WHILST FLN. A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE WILL THEN
DEVELOP ACROSS THE ATLANTIC ON THURSDAY ARRIVING IN THE BRITISH ISLES BY
MIDDAY. THERE MAY BE BRIEF RESPITES ON TUESDAY ACROSS THE N AND ACROSS THE
S ON WEDNESDAY BUT STRG WINDS ARE EXP ACROSS ALL PORTPATRICK SEA AREAS THROUGHOUT
MUCH OF THE PERIOD. GALES ARE MOST PROB IN BAILEY FAEROES AND SE ICELAND
ON WEDNESDAY THEN HEBRIDES AND FAIR ISLE EARLY THURSDAY
